    <string name="grounding_intro_desc">This technique will help you ground yourself during a panic attack or overthinking by connecting with the present moment through your senses.</string>
    <string name="grounding_see_title">5 things you can SEE</string>
    <string name="grounding_see_desc">Look around you. Tap a circle for each object you identify (a lamp, a shadow, a color…).</string>
    <string name="grounding_touch_title">4 things you can TOUCH</string>
    <string name="grounding_touch_desc">Feel the texture of things (your clothes, the chair, the wall). Tap a circle for each.</string>
    <string name="grounding_hear_title">3 things you can HEAR</string>
    <string name="grounding_hear_desc">Pay attention to sounds (the wind, a clock, your breath). Tap a circle when you hear them.</string>
    <string name="grounding_smell_title">2 things you can SMELL</string>
    <string name="grounding_smell_desc">Find two scents around you (your perfume, coffee, the room). Tap a circle when you notice them.</string>
    <string name="grounding_taste_title">1 thing you can TASTE</string>
    <string name="grounding_taste_desc">Identify a taste in your mouth (your saliva, a mint, water). Tap the circle to finish.</string>

    <string name="balloon_intro_desc">Sometimes, holding onto a thought causes tension. Write down what frustrates or worries you, and release it visually to lighten its weight from your mind.</string>
